snippet.textDisplay:
This song is so amazing that I have listened to it more than 30 times per my iPhone within 3 weeks. Didn't know Clinto Cerejo is talented music composer; I knew of him only as a singer. First time I heard I liked it but not as much as Clinton's other compositions Aisi Bani and Baina. It starts with really long music before the vocal; however, it is that music that is amazing that sets the mood and tempo of the whole composition.

This starts with really funky piano harmony followed by bass guitar and lead guitar raaga that continues until 2:30 minute, when the lead guitar loop starts; really scintillating! By the time the vocal starts at minute 3, you are completely hooked.

This is the kind of music that love to hear, along with Cinton's other great compositions for Coke Studio like Aisi Bani, Baina, and Banjara all of which are great fusion of Indian classical and rock.

Great going Clinton!
